description:
Consciousness

Let me introduce my self, I am a limitless being who are beyond time and space. The big and wide eyes, the most powerful being in this dimension.

I am also a flash of wind, a land and a highway leading towards ME whom bounded by time and space, that is now living inside a Jar.

But I have to save myself, a limited being which is trapped by space and time inside the confinement of Jar, which at first I thought it was protecting me but now instead it destroys me. Slowly but surely/s t e p  b y  s t e p. 

I, who are limitless, will be no longer let another me, as a being which has it's limits, linger in a Jar for so long. Not anymore. So, me as a limited being won't be trapped easily by false things.

In order to be able to love another I of me as a limitless being and the path to my Higher Self completely.

I heard the faintness from the Jar.
"Save me from every illusions and weariness, O my spirit and soul."


12/04/21

Watercolor on cold press paper 200gsm
3505 × 3306 Pixel

Personal use Only
